5. The Treasure Boxes (Sum of Array) 
Story: 
A hero finds n treasure boxes, each with some coins. 
He opens them one by one and counts the coins. 
�
�
 Find the total coins using recursion. 
Input: 
● First line: integer n 
● Second line: n integers (coins in each box). 
Output: 
● Sum of coins. 
Constraints: 
● 1 <= n <= 100 
● 1 <= coins[i] <= 1000 


CODE :
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int sumCoins(int coins[], int index, int n) {
    if (index == n) return 0;
    return coins[index] + sumCoins(coins, index + 1, n);
}

int main() {
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    int coins[n];
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
        cin >> coins[i];
    }
    cout << sumCoins(coins, 0, n);
    return 0;
}
